        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 2:17PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 217 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Masonville, or near Fort Collins, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fort Collins, northern Loveland, Windsor, Timnath, Masonville,
Drake and Horsetooth Mountain.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
